<subSubSection id="6CFE657D8636550D37A469BB86EAFA47" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="245B36F68636550D37A469BB8073FD42" blockId="3.[151,1437,410,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D37A469BB8501FE4C" bold="true" box="[151,279,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body length 10.7–12.6 mm, antennae composed of 
<number id="922C24D18636550D34B569BB87C6FE4C" box="[902,976,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="18.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="17.0">17–19</number>
articles, commonly 
<number id="922C24D18636550D33F169BB80F6FE4C" box="[1218,1248,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="18.0">18</number>
+ 
<number id="922C24D18636550D33C069BB8107FE4C" box="[1267,1297,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="18.0">18</number>
; 
<number id="922C24D18636550D322D69BB813BFE4C" box="[1310,1325,410,436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
ocelli on each side arranged in 
<number id="922C24D18636550D36AE69E185BAFE22" box="[413,428,448,474]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
horizontal rows; Tömösváry’s organ moderately large, rounded, almost equal to the adjoining ocelli; 
<number id="922C24D18636550D365469C48560FE07" box="[359,374,485,511]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="922C24D18636550D36B469C48580FE07" box="[391,406,485,511]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
moderately small sharp coxosternal teeth; porodont feebly slender, posterolateral to lateral tooth; all tergites without sharp posterior triangular projections; legs 
<number id="922C24D18636550D331B6A2B8050FDDC" box="[1064,1094,522,548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="14.0">14</number>
and 
<number id="922C24D18636550D33B16A2B80B6FDDC" box="[1154,1184,522,548]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="15.0">15</number>
thicker than anterior ones in female, still more in male; coxal pores 
<number id="922C24D18636550D35FC6A1186E9FDB2" box="[719,767,560,586]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
, ovate to round, arranged in one row; female gonopods with 
<number id="922C24D18636550D37E16A7484F7FD97" box="[210,225,597,623]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="922C24D18636550D37C26A748516FD97" box="[241,256,597,623]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
moderately thick, bullet–shaped spurs, second article with a long terminal thorn pointing backwards; apical claw simple, with two unconspicuous basal lateral denticles; male gonopods short and small, only a small hemispherical bulge, with 
<number id="922C24D18636550D35266A818632FD42" box="[533,548,672,698]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
long setae on the surface, tip slightly sclerotised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="245B36F68636550D37F66AE480AAFCFC" blockId="3.[151,1437,410,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D37F66AE48572FD27" bold="true" box="[197,356,709,735]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Spinulation.</emphasis>
Owing to a misprint, legs spinulation of 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D34566AE48026FD26" box="[869,1072,709,734]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinipes">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D34566AE48026FD26" box="[869,1072,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">H. longispinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not been included in the original description of this species (
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078636550D350B6ACB86FFFCFC" author="Ma" box="[568,745,746,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Ma, H. Q., Pei, S. J. &amp; Zhu, M. S. (2009) A new species of the Genus Hessebius Verhoeff, 1941 (Lithobiomorpha: Lithobiidae). Entomological News, 20, 195 - 200." type="journal article" year="2009">
Ma 
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D355B6ACB86B5FCFB" box="[616,675,746,771]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="922C24D18636550D35996ACB86FFFCFC" box="[682,745,746,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This data is reported here as in 
<tableCitation id="6966034D8636550D335F6ACB80A1FCFC" box="[1132,1207,746,772]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,239,820,844]" captionText="TABLE 2. Hessebius longispinipes Ma, Pei &amp; Zhu, 2009: leg spinulation; letters in brackets indicate variable spines. leg pairs ventral dorsal" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Tab. 
<number id="922C24D18636550D33956ACB80A1FCFC" box="[1190,1207,746,772]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
