<subSubSection id="6CFE657D8636550A37F66DEB8630FE4F" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="245B36F68636550D37F66DEB8566F8CC" blockId="3.[151,1437,1333,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D37F66DEB8529FA1C" bold="true" box="[197,319,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
In a paper on Mongolian centipedes, 
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078636550D34356DEB87B0FA1C" author="Loksa" box="[774,934,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Loksa, I. (1978) Chilopoden aus der Mongolei (Arthropoda: Tracheata: Chilopoda). Annales Historico - Naturales Musaei Nationalis Hungarici, 70, 111 - 120." type="journal article" year="1978">
Loksa (
<number id="922C24D18636550D346C6DEB878BFA1C" box="[863,925,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1978.0">1978</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the new species 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D33DF6DEA8515F9F1" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Schizotergitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styliferus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D33DF6DEA8515F9F1" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Schizotergitius styliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on material from “Bajanchongor aimak [= province]: Cagen Bodg ul Gebirge, Quelle Toorin bulag, 
<quantity id="E31C9B138636550D37D96E348520F9D7" box="[234,310,1557,1583]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="km" value="13.0">13 km</quantity>
O vom Grenzposten Caganbulag im Cagan Bogd ul Gebirge, 
<quantity id="E31C9B138636550D331B6E348090F9D7" box="[1064,1158,1557,1583]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
” (
<number id="922C24D18636550D33966E3480A4F9D7" box="[1189,1202,1557,1583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
Ƥ, 
<typeStatus id="FB5F88548636550D33D26E348176F9D7" box="[1249,1376,1557,1583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Holotypus</typeStatus>
) and “Gobi Altaj aimak [= province]: zwischen Schargyn Gobi und Beger nuur, cca 
<quantity id="E31C9B138636550D33076E1B8068F9AC" box="[1076,1150,1594,1620]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="km" value="20.0">20 km</quantity>
O von Somon Chalium, Chuural cacran, 
<quantity id="E31C9B138636550D366B6E4185A4F982" box="[344,434,1632,1658]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="1700.0">1700 m</quantity>
” (
<number id="922C24D18636550D36E36E4185CBF982" box="[464,477,1632,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
<number id="922C24D18636550D36D76E7E860EF982" box="[484,536,1631,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="3.1">3, 1</number>
Ƥ, 
<typeStatus id="FB5F88548636550D35776E4186ADF982" box="[580,699,1632,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Paratypes</typeStatus>
), in south-west 
<collectingCountry id="5CF376668636550D34416E4187FEF982" box="[882,1000,1632,1658]" name="Mongolia" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. This species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="FB5F88548636550D37A46EA484DCF967" box="[151,202,1669,1695]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
specimens. Although 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D36E16EA48628F966" box="[466,574,1669,1694]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Schizotergitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styliferus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D36E16EA48628F966" box="[466,574,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">styliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been originally assigned to the Central Asiatic genus 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D33DD6EA4855EF93C" authority="Verhoeff, 1930" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1930" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Schizotergitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D33DD6EA4818DF966" box="[1262,1435,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Schizotergitius</emphasis>
Verhoeff, 
<number id="922C24D18636550D36386E8B855EF93C" box="[267,328,1706,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1930.0">1930</number>
</taxonomicName>
, it clearly belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D35706E8A8766F93C" authority="Verhoeff, 1941" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1941" box="[579,880,1706,1732]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D35706E8A86ACF93C" box="[579,698,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Hessebius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078636550D35F26E8B8766F93C" author="Verhoeff" box="[705,880,1706,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Verhoeff, K. W. (1941) Asyanin zoogeografiyasi ve hayvan sistematige hakkinda. Asiatische Beitrage. II. Turkische Chilopoden. Istambul Universitesi Orman Fakultesi Dergisi, 6 B, 85 - 117." type="journal article" year="1941">
Verhoeff, 
<number id="922C24D18636550D34056E8B8766F93C" box="[822,880,1706,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D34B26E8B8041F93C" bold="true" box="[897,1111,1706,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">new combination</emphasis>
) by the shape of the female gonopods (see 
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078636550D36636EF185F3F912" author="Loksa" box="[336,485,1744,1770]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Loksa, I. (1978) Chilopoden aus der Mongolei (Arthropoda: Tracheata: Chilopoda). Annales Historico - Naturales Musaei Nationalis Hungarici, 70, 111 - 120." type="journal article" year="1978">
Loksa 
<number id="922C24D18636550D36976EF185F3F912" box="[420,485,1744,1770]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1978.0">1978</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 
<number id="922C24D18636550D351A6EF1866DF912" box="[553,635,1744,1770]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="27.29">27, 29</number>
). The other characters reported in the original description of this species also agree well with the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D35FF6ED4875FF8F6" box="[716,841,1781,1806]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D35FF6ED4875FF8F6" box="[716,841,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Hessebius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
here reported and those of 
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078636550D33926ED48171F8F7" author="Verhoeff" box="[1185,1383,1781,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Verhoeff, K. W. (1941) Asyanin zoogeografiyasi ve hayvan sistematige hakkinda. Asiatische Beitrage. II. Turkische Chilopoden. Istambul Universitesi Orman Fakultesi Dergisi, 6 B, 85 - 117." type="journal article" year="1941">
Verhoeff (
<number id="922C24D18636550D322D6ED48148F8F7" box="[1310,1374,1781,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1941.0">1941</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078636550D37A46F3B857AF8CC" author="Zalesskaja" box="[151,364,1818,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Zalesskaja, N. T. (1978) Identification book of the lithobiomorph centipedes of the USSR (Chilopoda: Lithobiomorpha). Nauka publ., Moscow, 211 pp. [in Russian]" type="book" year="1978">
Zalesskaja (
<number id="922C24D18636550D36106F3B8575F8CC" box="[291,355,1818,1844]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1978.0">1978</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="245B36F68636550D37F66F6185E8F817" blockId="3.[151,1437,1333,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D37F66F618541F8A1" box="[197,343,1856,1881]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Schizotergitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styliferus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D37F66F618541F8A1" box="[197,343,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">H. styliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems also strictly related to 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758636550D358E6F618797F8A1" box="[701,897,1856,1881]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinipes">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48636550D358E6F618797F8A1" box="[701,897,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">H. longispinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="6966034D8636550D34A16F6187C9F8A2" box="[914,991,1856,1882]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,242,451,475]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,607,1923]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 4. Range and main morphological characters of Sino – Mongolian species of Hessebius Verhoeff, 1941: H." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/709B667E8632550937A469E2818BFE23" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" tableUuid="709B667E8632550937A469E2818BFE23">
Tab. 
<number id="922C24D18636550D34FC6F6187C9F8A2" box="[975,991,1856,1882]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="4.0">4</number>
</tableCitation>
) and probably they belong to a same group of species. Both share morphological characters such as the general size, the number and arrangement of the ocelli, the shape of the coxosternum and porodont, the number and shape of the spurs of the female gonopods, the characteristic shape of the dorsal terminal part of the second article of the female gonopods, strongly extending backwards.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="245B36F68631550A37F668B98630FE4F" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,439]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
They differ in characters such as the number of antennal articles, 
<number id="922C24D18631550A34C668B98005FF4A" box="[1013,1043,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="17.0">17</number>
+ 
<number id="922C24D18631550A331768B98067FF4A" box="[1060,1137,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="18.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="17.0">17–19</number>
+ 
<quantity id="E31C9B138631550A33B068B980D7FF4A" box="[1155,1217,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.826" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="19.0">19 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A33F968B98182FF49" box="[1226,1428,152,177]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinipes">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A33F968B98182FF49" box="[1226,1428,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. longispinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<number id="922C24D18631550A37A4689C84A3FF2F" box="[151,181,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="20.0">20</number>
+ 
<quantity id="E31C9B138631550A37F7689C8516FF2F" box="[196,256,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="20.0">20 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A363B689C8581FF2E" box="[264,407,189,214]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stilyferus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A363B689C8581FF2E" box="[264,407,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. stilyferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in some detail of the spinulation of legs, chiefly the presence of DaC on legs 
<quantity id="E31C9B138631550A3252689C84B8FF04" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.048" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="2.286" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="12.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="9.0">9–15 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A378768C38562FF03" box="[180,372,226,251]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinipes">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A378768C38562FF03" box="[180,372,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. longispinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on legs 
<quantity id="E31C9B138631550A36EE68C38655FF04" box="[477,579,226,252]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="2.794" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="13.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="11.0">11–15 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A357A68C386CFFF03" box="[585,729,226,251]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Schizotergitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styliferus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A357A68C386CFFF03" box="[585,729,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. styliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the VmF in all the legs in 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A337568C38113FF03" box="[1094,1285,226,251]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinipes">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A337568C38113FF03" box="[1094,1285,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. longispinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only in legs 
<quantity id="E31C9B138631550A37A469298515FEDA" box="[151,259,264,290]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="3.556" metricValueMin="2.794" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="12.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="11.0">11–14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A363F692985B3FED9" box="[268,421,264,289]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Schizotergitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styliferus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A363F692985B3FED9" box="[268,421,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. styliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both characters may show however some variation in 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A336E692980E6FEDA" box="[1117,1264,264,290]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lithobiidae</taxonomicName>
; in 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A322C6929818AFED9" box="[1311,1436,264,289]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A322C6929818AFED9" box="[1311,1436,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Hessebius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
variation in spinulation has been documented in 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A35D2690C8779FEBE" box="[737,879,301,326]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbipes">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A35D2690C8779FEBE" box="[737,879,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. barbipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078631550A34AE690C8028FEBF" author="Eason" box="[925,1086,301,327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" refString="Eason, E. H. (1981) On some new and little known southern Asiatic species of Lithobiidae (Chilopoda, Lithobiomorpha). Entomologica scandinavica, 12, 327 - 338." type="journal article" year="1981">
Eason (
<number id="922C24D18631550A34C4690C8023FEBF" box="[1015,1077,301,327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="1981.0">1981</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="40754B078631550A334A690C818EFEBF" author="Negrea" box="[1145,1432,301,327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" refString="Negrea, S. &amp; Matic, Z. (1995) Etude comparative de la variabilite des trois populations de Hessebius barbipes (Porat, 1893) (Chilopoda: Lithobiidae). Soil Fauna of Israel, 1, 29 - 39." type="journal article" year="1995">
Negrea &amp; Matic (
<number id="922C24D18631550A327D690C8199FEBF" box="[1358,1423,301,327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Worth notice is that the collecting sites of 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A359469738756FE93" box="[679,832,338,363]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Schizotergitius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styliferus">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A359469738756FE93" box="[679,832,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. styliferus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are ca 
<quantity id="E31C9B138631550A34A8697387EEFE94" box="[923,1016,338,364]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="km" value="380.0">380 km</quantity>
far one from another and 
<quantity id="E31C9B138631550A320C6973818BFE94" box="[1343,1437,338,364]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="km" value="600.0">600 km</quantity>
southwestward from the only locality known of 
<taxonomicName id="E3E44D758631550A35F469598790FE69" box="[711,902,376,401]" class="Chilopoda" family="Lithobiidae" genus="Hessebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lithobiomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispinipes">
<emphasis id="1690EAE48631550A35F469598790FE69" box="[711,902,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">H. longispinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the relationships between the two taxa deserve further investigation.
</paragraph>
